comments: I have generally had good experiences with doctors myself in getting the tests I need and getting the doctor to listen to my needs. I don't go too often to the doctors though. I also make an effort to speak clear and concisely and not show excessive emotion so the doctor would see I'm level headed. I do worry that in future I may have trouble getting certain things I want from doctors due to countless stories I have heard from friends/family and in the news about doctors being dismissive of certain symptoms, (which could be indicative of a serious illness) especially for women, which concerns me.

comments: One of the problems with visiting Drs is time. It always feels so rushed. When symptoms cannot be explained it's nice to hear why they cannot be explained. If other patients are having similar symptoms. If there is a bug going round causing this. If there could be other underlying causes. It is always nicer if the Dr acknowledges how things impact your life (using a scale 1-10) that they can then measure against when/if you go back. Offer things that might help even if they don;t know the cause. Ask you to come back or do a phone check in 4 weeks later to see if symptoms persist. Often if you feel unheard you don;t bother going back and that can be dangerous.
